{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is cross-module handoff (collectors -> aggregation payload -> summary step), not a single pure function (MOCK-MISS). Real OS/network/subprocess is not required to reproduce this specific failure; source clients can be in-process fakes returning controlled payloads (REAL-INFRA, INTEGRATION-BRAKE a=no). Correctness does not depend on model output quality, only on what is passed into the step (LLM-DEP=no; disqualifying higher level text: 'content passed to the summary-generation step'). No multi-agentic chain (MULTI-STEP=no).","test_description":"Wire real aggregation/report modules together with three fake source adapters; execute one run and assert the exact input object sent to the summary-generation interface contains fields from metrics endpoint, issue tracker API, and deployment log.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is module interaction/error-propagation behavior: one source failure must be transformed into section-level fallback state and continue report assembly (MOCK-MISS -> Integration). Can be reproduced with an in-process failing adapter/exception; no real network or subprocess is required for this behavior (INTEGRATION-BRAKE a=no). Behavior text is about fallback note and non-abort, not model judgment quality (INTEGRATION-BRAKE b=no). No multi-agentic sequence (c,d=no). Rejected higher level with disqualifying text: '`data unavailable` note ... rather than aborting' specifies control-flow/fallback handling.","test_description":"Run report generation with real orchestrator modules, configure one source adapter to raise timeout/unavailable, keep the other two successful, and assert output report contains that section's `data unavailable` marker while process completes and returns a deliverable report artifact.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on generation quality/faithfulness of the summary itself, which is model-output dependent; stubs would mask factual-mismatch failures (LLM-DEP=yes, MOCK-HIDE=yes). Even with deterministic assertions, this behavior evaluates what the model says about data, not wrapper plumbing. Rejected Workflow: behavior describes a single summary-generation judgment, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence (disqualifying text: 'The narrative summary accurately represents...').","test_description":"Execute the real summary-generation dependency on curated fixtures with known key metrics/issues/deploy counts; score outputs for factual consistency against source values (e.g., exact-value checks/tolerance rules) across repeated runs and fail on omission/inversion/hallucinated values.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.8,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This behavior explicitly requires end-to-end delivery to a real inbox, crossing real network/email infrastructure and external APIs (REAL-INFRA=yes -> System). In-process mocks can hide SMTP/API auth, TLS, provider acceptance, and inbox delivery issues (MOCK-HIDE=yes). Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior asserts transport completion ('reaches ... inbox correctly'), not model decision quality; any summary content can be fixed fixture for this test focus.","test_description":"Run the scheduled script (or equivalent entrypoint) against reachable staging/internal endpoints and real email delivery service credentials, then verify the configured mailbox receives the message with expected subject/body sections and recipient list.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.15,"Workflow":0.04}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure spans real delivery failure mode plus cross-run persistence/retry semantics. To catch real failures, test should exercise actual unreachable transport behavior and real filesystem persistence across executions (REAL-INFRA=yes). Mocks can miss real socket/provider failure classes and restart-boundary persistence bugs (MOCK-HIDE=yes). Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior is delivery fallback/retry orchestration, not model-quality or multi-agentic decision chain (disqualifying text: 'email delivery service is unreachable ... saved to a local file ... retried on the next scheduled run').","test_description":"First run: execute script with email endpoint intentionally unreachable and assert report file is written to configured local retry/spool path. Second scheduled run (separate process invocation) with email restored: assert previously saved report is retried/sent successfully and local retry artifact is cleared/marked sent.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
